HEADWORD: Sabbat
<hw>Sab"bat</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Sabbath</er>.]</ety> <def>In mediaeval demonology, the nocturnal
assembly in which demons and sorcerers were thought to celebrate their
orgies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

